    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>cauliflower</strong> into florets and the <strong>stem[s]</strong> into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>cauliflower</strong> <strong>florets</strong> and <strong>chopped stem[s]</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the dish in the oven for 10-15 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-pie-with-roast-waxy-potatoes-and-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the cauliflower is in the oven, grate your <strong>cheddar</strong> <strong>cheese</strong> and <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Peel and grate your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>waxy</strong> <strong>potatoes </strong>in half, lengthways</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-pie-with-roast-waxy-potatoes-and-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>grated cheddar </strong>and<strong> half </strong>the<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>with your <strong>cornflour</strong> in a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) and mix until the cheese is coated in the flour</p><p>Add 175ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [230ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>milk </strong>to the pan with the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>Dijon mustard </strong>(save the rest for later!) a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong>, then cook over a medium heat for 3-4 min, stirring frequently, or until the cheese has melted and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-pie-with-roast-waxy-potatoes-and-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a <strong>baking</strong> <strong>paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>thyme</strong>, 2/3 of the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-pie-with-roast-waxy-potatoes-and-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap your <strong>puff</strong> <strong>pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-pie-with-roast-waxy-potatoes-and-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, remove the dish from the oven and mix the <strong>cheese</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> through the roasted cauliflower</p><p>Top the dish with the <strong>rolled</strong> <strong>pastry</strong>, brush with a little <strong>milk </strong>and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Return the dish to the oven for a further 20 min or until the pastry is puffed up, golden and cooked through \u2013\u00a0this is your <strong>cauliflower cheese pie</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-pie-with-roast-waxy-potatoes-and-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>Dijon</strong> <strong>mustard</strong> and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> in a bowl with the <strong>cider</strong> <strong>vinegar</strong>, 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 1 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 1/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>mustard dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and toss through the mustard dressing \u2013\u00a0this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cauliflower-cheese-pie-with-roast-waxy-potatoes-and-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cauliflower cheese pie</strong> with the <strong>roast waxy potatoes </strong>and <strong>dressed</strong> <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Discard the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
